HEADWORD: Callet
<hw>Cal"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Ir. & Gael.
<ets>caile</ets> a country woman, strumpet.]</ety> <def>A trull or
prostitute; a scold or gossip.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>callat</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

